      "role": "user",
      "content": "that makes sense. so if we follow that logic, isn't any kind of govt oversight—even stuff meant to stop misinformation or protect kids—inherently a step toward a surveillance state that kills real discourse? it seems like there's no way to regulate without destroying the very freedom the net was built on.",
