      "content": "Yes, the premise of the \"chilling effect\" logically extends to argue that *any* government oversight, regardless of its benevolent intent, is a corrosive step toward authoritarianism. The moment the state gains the power to define \"misinformation\" or \"harm,\" it gains the power to dictate acceptable thought. This power, once granted, is never truly relinquished, inevitably leading to a surveillance apparatus that prioritizes control over genuine, messy, and vital public discourse.",
      "source": "target",
